I get up from bed at the usual time, eat a usual breakfast of two sunny-side
 up eggs with bacon, and take my usual walking route through the vast countrysid
e to clear my mind.
 So many years now, it has been.
 But even after all this time, every time I look around and see the beautiful
 grassy hills, I feel ever closer to the world.
 As if I am yet another step closer to finding the meaning of life.
 Or finding God.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
I shiver a little.
 My thin sweater keeps me rudely aware of the briskness of morning in early
 September.
 I can't say it feels like autumn at this time of year, but the mornings
 are a chilling reminder of what is to come.
 Leaves fall, followed by snow, followed by spirits.
 I hate winter.
\end_layout

