 Just like every morning, some train of thought brings me back to him.
 Just like every morning, I let tears fall down my face, with only the clouds
 and the warbling birds as witnesses.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
My therapist told me to stop writing for a while—that letting my mind run
 wild might prevent me from ever getting past this.
 But I am already at a point in life where there is no use to rid myself
 of these emotions, of those memories.
 After all, most of my sixty years revolved him.
 How curious it is that people want me to go 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

back to normal
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

