 His face.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
I turn back to the shelf and take the picture frame out from underneath
 the pile of loose sheet music.
 And I look at him again.
 He looks so happy in that photo of us.
 Whether he was happy being there with me or because he had some tune stuck
 in his head, I will never know.
 I turn the frame to read again the newspaper clipping I taped on the back.
 A black and white picture of him playing at a concert in some big concert
 hall.
 The caption: 
