\begin_layout Standard
Michelle has best friend in drama; she and her boyfriend are the stars
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ami injured his hand when he was younger, led to motor issues with excessive
 practice for the rest of his life (despite having perfect, relaxed technique)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Recurring Hand Injury
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Why not stop a few years then pick up where you left off"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And live all that time without music?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Talks about God
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Michelle grew up in a Catholic family, but slowly felt more and more distanced
 from God.
 Through her interactions with Ami, she starts wondering about fate/destiny
 and the concept of free will.
 When she asks Ami what he thinks about God, he said he always committed
 himself to a life connected to music and those he cares about (referring
 to his family and Michelle) because if there is a God, it would satisfy
 him, and if there isn't, they only have each other.
 Michelle is greatly moved by this, and regains her faith in the power of
 humanity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Ami's Death vs Michelle's Success
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
How tragic it is that the genius who soared above us all lost everything
 to let me experience emerging from the treetops.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Teaching
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Michelle considers teaching to be a very modest 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

fallback
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 career.
 However, by the end, she realizes how much she was able to subtly learn
 from Ami, and realizes that being able to communicate teachings like that
 is a very rare and special talent.
 She ends up feeling unworthy to teach.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Happy Memories
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Michelle and Ami have a series of very special memories, including both
 of them trying to surprise the other for Christmas.
 The hand injury to Ami happens sometime in February before Valentine's
 Day, and Michelle later turns down a (male) friend's invitation to go out
 on Valentine's Day, much to her own surprise (she should be shown to have
 some level of attraction to this friend before).
 She realizes that in some ways, she assumed she would be doing something
 with Ami.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section*
Romance
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Michelle and Ami only ever have a platonic relationship.
 However, in her flashback Michelle often muses about whether or not they
 could have ever been lovers.
 Eventually, she becomes convinced that Ami never loved her romantically,
 since he was too busy facing forward to be able to consider her in any
 way unless she was willing to run alongside him.
\end_layout

